          <title>
            <string language="sl">Žejni labod</string>
            <string language="en">Thirsty swam</string>
            <string language="x-mt-de">Durstig schwamm</string>
            <string language="x-mt-fr">Altéré a nagé</string>
            <string language="x-mt-pt">Thirsty nadou</string>
            <string language="x-mt-it">Assetato ha nuotato</string>
            <string language="x-mt-el">Διψασμένος κολύμπησε</string>
            <string language="x-mt-es">Sediento nadó</string>
          </title>
          <language>x-none</language>
          <description>
            <string language="sl">Živali, ki jih povsod okrog obkroža voda, so prav tako žejne kot mi. Labod na fotografiji se je pravkar odžejal, iz kljuna mu še kaplja voda.</string>
            <string language="en">Animals that are surrounded by water can still get thirsty. Swan on the picture has just made a sip - drops of water are still visible on his beak</string>
          </description>
          <keyword>
            <string language="sl">labod</string>
            <string language="en">swan</string>
          </keyword>
          <keyword>
            <string language="sl">žeja</string>
            <string language="en">thirst</string>
          </keyword>
          <keyword>
            <string language="sl">voda</string>

          </keyword>
          <keyword>
            <string language="sl">bled</string>
            <string language="en">bled</string>
          </keyword>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-de">Tiere, die durch Wasser umgeben werden, können 
ruhig durstig erhalten. Schwan auf der Abbildung hat gerade 
einen sip gebildet - Tropfen des Wassers sind noch auf seinem Schnabel
sichtbar</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-fr">Les animaux qui sont entourés par l'eau peuvent 
immobile devenir altérés. Le cygne sur l'image a juste fait un
SIP - les gouttes d'eau sont encore visibles sur son bec</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-pt">Os animais que são cercados pela água podem 
imóvel começar thirsty. A cisne no retrato fêz apenas um sip 
- as gotas da água são ainda visíveis em seu bico</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-it">Gli animali che sono circondati da acqua possono 
tranquillo ottenere assetati. Lo swan sull'immagine ha fatto 
appena un sip - le gocce di acqua sono ancora visibili sul suo becco</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-el">Τα ζώα που περιβάλλονται από το ύδωρ μπορούν ακόμα 
να πάρουν διψασμένα. Ο κύκνος στην εικόνα έκανε μόλις μια 
γουλιά - οι απελευθερώσεις του ύδατος είναι ακόμα ορατές στο 
ράμφος του</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-es">Los animales que son rodeados por el agua pueden 
inmóvil conseguir sedientos. El cisne en el cuadro acaba de 
hacer un sip - las gotas del agua siguen siendo visibles en su pico</string>
          </description>
